    {
      "id": "/works/OL24318727W",
      "title": "Amygdalatropolis",
      "author": "B R Yeager",
      "coverId": 10836834,
      "firstPublishYear": 2017,
      "pages": 200,
      "rating": 4,
      "notes": "8/10 LOVED, the author clearly spent a lot of time on 4chan because holy shit it was accurate. it wasn’t even supposed to be a similar forum, it was just 4chan renamed lmao. it didn’t ever go the direction i thought it was going to, and i appreciated when it had the opportunity for gross out shock stuff and didn’t take it. just got close enough to give you the idea. the video game stuff near the end after his father died was 10/10 fantastic amazing. writing style was a lot but i liked it overall",
      "dateRead": "2026-04-02",
      "addedAt": "2026-04-11T04:30:05.262Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "/works/OL24861196W",
      "title": "Gone to See the River Man",
      "author": "Kristopher Triana",
      "coverId": 11745530,
      "firstPublishYear": 2020,
      "pages": 175,
      "rating": 2.5,
      "notes": "6/10 underwhelming, heard nothing but good stuff about this book but didn’t love it. apparently all splatterpunk is just WORSE than this though. i mean i didn’t hate it either, the story was fun and engaging and the river literally turning to blood and gore was sick. it was like a really cool music video. the ending was pretty predictable and underwhelming but the journey to get there was engaging and i was really eager to hear the ways the multiple stories played out. bonkered that its like, THE BEST though. the psychedelic/hallucinatory stuff was really really cool but the supernatural parts were lame as fuck",
